<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2025-12-03-the-roving-wazir-1.jpg" alt="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutilated_chessboard_problem#Related_problems" width="395" height="396" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-72221" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2025-12-03-the-roving-wazir-1.jpg 395w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2025-12-03-the-roving-wazir-1-300x300.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 395px) 100vw, 395px" /></p>
<p>A <em>wazir</em> is a fanciful chess piece that can move one square horizontally or vertically, but not diagonally. This one finds itself in the upper left corner of the board. Can it make its way to the lower right while visiting each square exactly once?</p>

<div class='easySpoilerWrapper' style=''>
