<tr><td class='easySpoilerRow' colspan='2' style=''><div id='spoilerDiv19988001' class='easySpoilerSpoils'  style='display:none; white-space:wrap; overflow:auto; vertical-align:middle;'>
</p>
<p>No. The nature of the wazir&#8217;s move means that it visits light and dark squares alternately. The board has 64 squares, and the piece begins on a light square, so a successful journey would end on a dark one. The target square is light, so the task is impossible. Simple enough!</p>
<p>
